Member Enumeration Documentation

enum RouteTypes::routeCostType
 

The types of route costs.

Enumeration values:
DISTANCE  DISTANCE, optimize length of route.
TIME  TIME, optimize time of route.
TIME_WITH_DISTURBANCES  TIME_WITH_DISTURBANCES, optimize time of route with distsurbances.
NBR_ROUTECOSTTYPE  Number of routeCostType.

routeCostType RouteTypes::costToRouteCostType (  byte  costA,
byte  costB,
byte  costC,
byte  costD
)  [static]
 

Route cost A,B,C,D to routeCostType.

The algorith for convertion is simple: If costA != 0 then it is DISTANCE, if costB != 0 then it is TIME, if costC != 0 then it is TIME_WITH_DISTURBANCES else it is TIME.

Parameters:
costA The route cost A.
costB The route cost B.
costC The route cost C.
costD The route cost D.
Returns:
The routeCostType for the route cost.
